                  </persName>
            . I am wife of 
               <persName id="t18230910-77-person888">
                  Christopher 
                  Fairbrother
               <interp inst="t18230910-77-person888" type="surname" value="Fairbrother"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-77-person888" type="given" value="Christopher"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-77-person888" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and sell oysters at the corner of Wild-court, Wild-street. On the 8th of August, I employed the prisoner to carry half a bushel of oysters for me. I was going with him - I had known him for months. I crossed the road in <placeName id="t18230910-77-crimeloc440">Darkhouse-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-77-crimeloc440" type="placeName" value="Darkhouse-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-77-crimeloc440" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-77-off438 t18230910-77-crimeloc440"></join>, to avoid the carts, and thought he was close behind me - but, on looking round, he was gone - he knew where I lived, for he told me so. I waited at home an hour; he did not come, but was taken in about three hours at Billingsgate. I said</p>
               <p>"Young man you have not carried my oysters home;" he used a dreadful expression, and said he had not carried an oyster that day - another man came and abused me also. I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. When you came to Billingsgate, you were very much intoxicated - A. I was not, I accused nobody but him of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-77-person889">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18230910-77-person889" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-77-person889" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-77-person889" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. The prosecutrix accused the prisoner of robbing her, and was positive to him - she was quite sober.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never had them; the man said if I produced the money for them, he would let me go.</p>
